TITLE_CONTRACT.P: Framework agreements for consultancy services within ICT.

SHORT_CONTRACT_DESCRIPTION.P: NAV IKT would like to enter into framework agreements for consultancy services within ICT. The contracts shall cover the need for competence which the awarding authority does not have access to in its own department at a given time or where there is a separate need for the assignment to be solved externally. The contracts can also be used for extra capacity.
The requested consultancy services are divided into the following areas of competence:
— Operation of IT systems and platforms,

The awarding authority plans to carry out a comprehensive renewal/modernisation of ICT (the Modernisation Project). Because of this the consultancy services contracts within ICT can be somewhat different to the estimates given in this notice. See the qualification documents for further information.
See the qualification documents for information on which units the contract is for.
Note: to register your interest in this notice and obtain any additional information please visit the Doffin web site at http://www.doffin.no/Search/Search_Switch.aspx?ID=226849.

ECONOMIC_OPERATORS_PERSONAL_SITUATION.P: (3) Self-declaration in compliance with Appendix 2 (HSE) of the Norwegian procurement regulations (national requirement);
The service provider is required to have a legally established company.
Norwegian service providers: company registration certificate from the Brønnøysund Register Centre;
Foreign service providers: certification of registration in a company register as described in the law in the country where the service provider is established.

EAF_CAPACITY_INFORMATION.P: The awarding authority will itself obtain an accounts analysis carried out by Experian, see www.experian.no.
If a tenderer believes that the analysis will not give a correct picture, further information is to be enclosed with the tender.

EAF_CAPACITY_MIN_LEVEL.P: The service provider is required to have good financial solidity. A credit rating of "credit worthy" or better is required.

T_CAPACITY_INFORMATION.P: — The service provider’s most important contracts in the last 3 years (per competence area that a request is sent for), including:
— A short description of the assignment, including the service provider’s contribution in the assignment,
The name and contact information of the contact person at the reference customer shall be included so that NAV can make contact if needed.
Form for relevant experience in annex 2 of the qualification documents. This shall be used when answering this point.
— Account of the company’s quality assurance system/control system, including the system for insuring the development and maintenance of competence and any certificates issued by independent bodies,
— The request for participation must state if the service provider is enclosing an account which is valid for all areas a request is given for,
— If a service provider encloses accounts aimed at each competence area a request is given for, they must be enclosed sorted per area and it must be clear which area the account is for.

T_CAPACITY_MIN_LEVEL.P: — Service providers are required to have relevant experience from similar assignments,
— A good and well functioning quality assurance system is required.

OPE_OBJECTIVE_CRITERIA.P: The awarding authority will invite at least 5 and a maximum of 15 of the qualified service providers per area of competence to give a tender, provided that a sufficient number of service providers are qualified.
The selection of service providers will be based on the following criteria from the qualification document’s point 2.4:

Service providers will be evaluated in the following way: service providers will be given a character for each qualification requirement on a points scale from 0 to 10, with 10 being the best. Each of these characters will be multiplied with the relevant weighting. This will give a ranking in each area which will form the basis for the selection.
